Ukraine Says May Form Grain Pool Involving Russia, Kazakhstan

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a   a n d   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 
2011-04-12T14:14:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/ukraine-says-may-form-grain-pool-involving-russia-kazakhstan.html
Ukraine , Russia and Kazakhstan may
join together in a so-called grain pool this year to coordinate
crop sales and share export facilities, Ukraine’s Deputy Economy
Minister Valeriy Muntiyan said.  “Ukraine, Russia and Kazakhstan may set up a grain pool
this year,” Muntiyan, who is also Ukraine’s representative at
the Commonwealth of Independent States, told reporters today in
the capital, Kiev, before a meeting between Ukrainian Prime
Minister Mykola Azarov with his Russian counterpart Vladimir Putin.  Russian Agriculture Minister  Yelena Skrynnik  put forward
plans in 2009 to share port facilities on the Black Sea.  To contact the reporters on this story:
